      "id": "PopularPost130092",
      "post_content": "Typically red and random. Roughly one third chance each turn to kill the creature, and two thirds to buff it. I guess you could put it on creatures you don't mind dying. Such as a rukh egg. If it gets buffed: nice, you got a 3/6 attacker. If it get's killed: well, then you got a 4/4 token. Or on a mindslicer, which would then be 7/6 (or have everyone discard their hands). Or put it on indestructible creatures. Or use it as a kill spell in some enchantment deck. Or whatever.... It's still a bad card, but interesting.",
      "posted_by": "majinara",
